Git Workflow Standards

---
description: Git Workflow Standards
alwaysApply: true
---

- Use feature branches from develop.
- Commit messages must be descriptive and reference issues.
- Every Pull Request should detail changes, how to test, and any doc updates.
- Enforce pre-commit/pre-push hooks to run tests, formatters, and linters automatically.
